Architecture Explanation

As illustrated above, client applications never communicate directly with the database servers.

Instead:

All client connections are established with MySQL Router.

Write requests received on Port 6446 are forwarded to the current Primary server.

Read requests received on Port 6447 are distributed among available Secondary servers.

If the Primary changes because of an automatic failover, Router immediately begins directing new write connections to the newly elected Primary without requiring any application changes.

This abstraction layer greatly simplifies application development while improving database availability.

Key Responsibilities of MySQL Router

MySQL Router performs several critical functions within an InnoDB Cluster environment:

Automatically routes write traffic to the Primary server.

Automatically routes read traffic to Secondary servers.

Continuously monitors cluster metadata.

Detects topology changes and failover events.

Hides cluster complexity from client applications.

Supports workload distribution across multiple servers.

Improves overall database availability.

Simplifies application connectivity.

Benefits of Using MySQL Router

Deploying MySQL Router in an enterprise environment offers numerous operational advantages.

1. Automatic Failover

If the Primary server becomes unavailable, Router automatically redirects new write connections to the newly elected Primary without requiring any manual intervention.

2. Read/Write Separation

Write operations are always directed to the Primary server, while read operations are automatically routed to Secondary servers.

This separation significantly reduces workload on the Primary server and improves cluster performance.

3. Simplified Application Design

Applications no longer need logic to discover the current Primary server.

Developers only configure a single Router endpoint.

4. High Availability

Database failover becomes transparent to client applications, minimizing downtime and improving service continuity.

5. Improved Scalability

Additional Secondary servers can be added to the cluster without modifying application configurations.

Router automatically recognizes new cluster members.

